The <b>Paris Kanellakis Theory and Practice Award</b> is granted yearly by the <organization wordnetid="108008335" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/30th_century.xml">
Association for Computing Machinery</link></organization>
 (ACM) to honor specific theoretical accomplishments that have had a significant and demonstrable effect on the practice of computing. It was instituted in memory of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../784/328784.xml">
computer scientist</link> <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<unfortunate wordnetid="109630641" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<victim wordnetid="110752093" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<academician wordnetid="109759069" confidence="0.8">
<scientist wordnetid="110560637" confidence="0.8">
<adult wordnetid="109605289" confidence="0.8">
<professional wordnetid="110480253" confidence="0.8">
<research_worker wordnetid="110523076" confidence="0.8">
<educator wordnetid="110045713" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../546/2979546.xml">
Paris Kanellakis</link></educator>
</research_worker>
</professional>
</adult>
</scientist>
</academician>
</causal_agent>
</victim>
</person>
</unfortunate>
</physical_entity>
, who died with his immediate family on <accident wordnetid="107301336" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../730/417730.xml">
American Airlines Flight 965</link></accident>
. The award is accompanied by a prize of $5,000 and is endowed by contributions from the Kanellakis family, with additional financial support provided by ACM's Special Interest Groups on Algorithms and Computational Theory (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../782/4356782.xml">
SIGACT</link>), Design Automaton (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../458/3751458.xml">
SIGDA</link>), Management of Data (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../519/5897519.xml">
SIGMOD</link>), and Programming Languages (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../658/1226658.xml">
SIGPLAN</link>), the ACM SIG Projects Fund, and individual contributions.
